Here's a simple HTML file with embedded CSS and JavaScript that displays "Nothing for you here" on the page. You can copy and paste the following code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nothing for You Here</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            color: #333;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5em;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Nothing for you here</h1>

    <script>
        // You can add any JavaScript functionality here if needed
        console.log("Page loaded: Nothing for you here");
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This code sets up a basic web page with a centered message and includes styling for the body and header. The JavaScript section currently just logs a message to the console when the page is loaded. You can expand it as needed!
